Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20wants%20to%20crack%20down.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMost%20incidents%2C%20like%20travelers%20re-entering%20through%20one-way%20exits%2C%20didn't%20have%20any%20%26quot%3Bevil%20intent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20wished%20you%20could%20skip%20the%20line%20at%20the%20airport%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20300%20people%20since%20March%202023%20have%20done%20just%20that%20by%20slipping%20past%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-tsa-agent-travel-tips-getting-through-security-frozen-water2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20TSA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20larger%20problem%20than%20we%20realized%2C%26quot%3B%20Transportation%20Security%20Administration%20spokesperson%20R.%20Carter%20Langston%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftravel%2F2024%2F04%2F04%2Fairport-security-tsa-stowaway%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Washington%20Post%20in%20a%20new%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stat%20marks%20a%20massive%20uptick%20over%20previous%20years%3B%20there%20were%20just%2029%20airport%20security%20breaches%20in%202019%20and%2072%20in%202022%2C%20the%20agency%20told%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELangston%20said%20the%20breaches%20were%20a%20%26quot%3Btrend%26quot%3B%20the%20TSA%20wants%20to%20crack%20down%20on.%20That%20said%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%26quot%3B%20of%20breaches%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20evil%20intent%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20Post%2C%20with%20most%20resulting%20from%20accidents%2C%20impatience%2C%20or%20people%20looking%20for%20misplaced%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20more%20than%20200%20breaches%20last%20year%2C%20people%20re-entered%20one-way%20exits%2C%20while%20in%2080%2C%20people%20evaded%20travel%20document%20checkers%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Post.%20In%20those%2080%20instances%2C%20all%20passengers%20were%20still%20screened%20by%20a%20metal%20detector%20or%20body%20scanner%2C%20Langston%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20noted%20that%20multiple%20incidents%20in%20recent%20months%20corroborate%20the%20new%20TSA%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%2C%20a%20passenger%20walked%20through%20an%20unstaffed%20body%20scanner.%20In%20a%20separate%20incident%20that%20same%20month%2C%20another%20flyer%20bypassed%20ID%20checks%20and%20flew%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20without%20a%20ticket.%20She%20was%20detained%20by%20the%20FBI%20upon%20her%20arrival%20but%20not%20charged%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TSA%20is%20testing%20new%20ways%20to%20stem%20security%20breaches%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported%2C%20including%20solid%20plastic%20or%20glass%20barriers%20in%20place%20of%20the%20nylon%20belts%20popularly%20used%20as%20line%20dividers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20one-way%20gates%20that%20close%20behind%20travelers%20when%20they%20pass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20improve%20the%20passenger%20experience%2C%20the%20TSA%20said%20in%20March%20it%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-self-service-security-screening-airport-test-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etest%20self-checkout%20style%20security%20screenings%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Harry%20Reid%20International%20Airport%20in%20Las%20Vegas%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20for%20TSA%20PreCheck%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F300-people-breached-airport-security-tsa-says-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712261388000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660ee62c16bde8d4ead5c4d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F300-people-breached-airport-security-tsa-says-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20TSA%20wants%20to%20crack%20down%2C%20it%20said%20most%20breaches%2C%20people%20reentering%20through%20one-way%20exits%2C%20weren't%20m